longBusinessSummary: Eastfield Resources Ltd., an exploration stage company, engages in the acquisition and exploration of mineral properties in Canada. It primarily explores for gold, copper, nickel, silver, molybdenum, cobalt, and platinum group metals. The company holds 100% interests in the Zymo property that consists of 33 claims and fractions covering an area of 9,195 hectares located in west-central British Columbia; Iron Lake located in south-central British Columbia, which consists of 21 claims covering an area of 8,035 hectares; and Big Valley project located in the mining towns of Wells and Barkerville, British Columbia. It also holds a 91.3% interest in the Indata property comprising 16 claims covering an area of 3,189 hectares located in British Columbia. Eastfield Resources Ltd. was founded in 1986 and is headquartered in Vancouver, Canada.
